<DOC><DOCNO> AP900602-0150 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-02-90 2242EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--RedBrigades     06-02 0124</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Red Brigades,0128</SECOND><HEAD>Red Brigades Terrorists Convicted in Senator's Slaying</HEAD><DATELINE>FORLI, Italy (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A court has sentenced nine leftist RedBrigades terrorists to life in prison after convicting them ofmurdering a Christian Democrat senator.   Roberto Ruffilli, a close friend and adviser to then PremierCiriaco De Mita, was shot to death in his home on April 16, 1988.Ruffilli was a key architect of institutional reform plans.   Three of the defendants were acquitted in the verdicts issuedFriday.   The leftist Red Brigades carried out scores of violent attacks inthe 1970s and early 1980s aimed at toppling the Italian government.   During that period, the Red Brigades kidnapped and killed AldoMoro, a former premier and president of the Christian Democrat Party.</TEXT></DOC>